{"word":"H1869 - דָּרַךְ - dârak - daw-rak' - Archer","slug":"H1869","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">דָּרַךְ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>dârak"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>daw-rak'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Archer"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D3;&#x05BC;&#x05E8;&#x05DA; - da&#x0302;rak</b> - <i>daw-rak'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>tread</i>; by implication to <i>walk</i>; also to <i>string</i> a bow (by treading on it in bending): - archer, bend, come, draw, go (over), guide, lead (forth), thresh, tread (down), walk."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H150\">H150</a>, <a href=\"#/H1870\">H1870</a>, <a href=\"#/H1871\">H1871</a>, <a href=\"#/H4096\">H4096</a>"}]}